  "prompt": "How does one juggle?",
  "response": "Learning to juggle involves several steps:\n\n1. Start with one ball\n- Practice throwing and catching a single ball from hand to hand at a consistent height\n\n2. Move to two balls\n- Hold one ball in each hand\n- Toss one ball in an arc to the other hand\n- When the first ball reaches its peak, toss the second ball\n- Practice this back and forth\n\n3. Progress to three balls\n- Start with two balls in one hand, one in the other\n- Throw the first ball in an arc\n- When it reaches its peak, throw the second ball\n- When the second ball reaches its peak, throw the third ball\n- Create a consistent rhythm and pattern\n- Practice the cascade pattern (balls cross in an arc)\n\n4. Key tips\n- Keep your eyes level\n- Throw balls to a consistent height\n- Use your wrist, not your whole arm\n- Practice consistently\n- Start slowly and be patient\n\n5. Practice techniques\n- Start near a bed or wall to catch dropped balls easily\n- Practice in short sessions\n- Don't get discouraged\n\n6. Once comfortable, you can learn more advanced juggling patterns and techniques\n\nConsistent practice is the most important factor in learning to juggle.",
